---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Advisory">
  <h1>Advisory</h1>
  <p class="muted">Financial decision review before capital commitment</p>

  <p>
    Advisory engagements are used prior to signing, funding, guaranteeing,
    or voting on a material financial commitment.
  </p>

  <p>
    The purpose is to define the commitment in writing,
    identify primary failure paths,
    and make downside allocation explicit before execution.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section class="offer">
    <h2><a href="/decision-framing">Decision Framing</a></h2>
    <p class="muted">Early-stage transaction definition</p>

    <p>
      Used when a transaction is forming but the commitment boundary
      and embedded assumptions remain unclear.
    </p>

    <h3>Output</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>One-sentence decision definition</li>
      <li>List of embedded assumptions</li>
      <li>Initial downside mapping</li>
      <li>Required open items before advancement</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
      Fixed-fee engagement. Single defined decision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="offer">
    <h2><a href="/commitment-review">Commitment Review</a></h2>
    <p class="muted">Pre-execution structural risk assessment</p>

    <p>
      Used when a financial commitment is near execution
      and loss mechanics must be tested under stress conditions.
    </p>

    <h3>Deliverable</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Written decision definition</li>
      <li>Failure mode mapping</li>
      <li>Responsibility allocation analysis</li>
      <li>Preconditions required at close</li>
      <li>Eligibility verdict: Proceed · Hold · Do not proceed</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
      Fixed-fee engagement. Scoped in advance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    <a href="mailto:sercoidea@gmail.com">sercoidea@gmail.com</a>
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Include: decision, materials available, and execution timeline.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .muted { color: var(--muted); }
  .offer { margin: 1.25rem 0; }
</style>
